┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 API ENDPOINT MAPPING                        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ GET /categories                                             │
│ └─> Returns: List<String> of all unique categories          │
│     Executes: findAllCategories() from MySQL                │
│                                                              │
│ GET /products                                               │
│ └─> Returns: List<Product> - all products (paginated ideal) │
│     Executes: findAll() from MySQL                           │
│                                                              │
│ GET /products/{id}                                          │
│ └─> Returns: Optional<Product> by exact ID                  │
│     Executes: findById(id) from MySQL                        │
│                                                              │
│ GET /products?category=electronics                          │
│ └─> Returns: Filtered products by category                  │
│     Executes: findByCategory(category) from MySQL           │
│     Note: Category filtering uses structured DB             │
│                                                              │
│ GET /products?query=smartphone                              │
│ └─> Returns: Full-text search results                       │
│     Executes: Elasticsearch query (title OR description)    │
│     Maps back to Product entities for API response          │
│                                                              │
│ Priority Logic (in ProductController):                      │
│ 1. If query param provided → Elasticsearch search           │
│ 2. Else if category param provided → MySQL filter           │
│ 3. Else → Return all products from MySQL                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


